headline: Gilead Sciences’s Q2 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: Gilead Sciences delivered a better-than-expected second quarter, propelled by the strong performance of its HIV portfolio and the launch of Yeztugo, its twice-yearly injectable for HIV prevention. Management attributed the 7% year-over-year HIV growth to robust demand for Biktarvy and Descovy, along with effective commercial execution.
